\subsection{Dynamical Solutions}
For each candidate orbital period for KOI-72.X listed in Table \ref{tab:pttv}, we perform a series of numerical N-body integrations using TTVFast \citep{Deck2014}.  We use the analytically predicted orbital parameters as inputs to the integrator at epoch $T0 (BJD - 2454900) = 53.67844$.  TTVFast predicts the times of transit of each planet in the N-body simulation, and the RVs of the star at the times of RV observation.  To determine the orbital parameters that best reproduce the observed transit times and RVs, we minimize the following statistic:

